definition.value: A L-phenylalanine derivative that is L-phenylalanine in which the amino group is replaced by a [(2S)-2-hydroxypropanoyl]amino group. It is a metabolite produced as a result of exercise in mice, racehorses, and humans which suppresses feeding and obesity.
A diadenosyl tetraphosphate compound having the two 5'-adenosyl residues attached at the P(1)- and P(4)-positions.
A hemoprotein that is the ferric (Fe(3+)) form of hemoglobin.
The anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxylic acid group of 1-pyrroline-2-carboxylic acid.
